---
// RA's real official mark (their compact "RA" monogram, cropped from
// Wikipedia's ResidentAdvisor_logo.png — a black glyph on a transparent
// background, matching the source used for File:ResidentAdvisor_logo.png
// on enwiki), not a hand-drawn approximation. Source master lives at
// assets-src/resident-advisor-logo-master.png (full-res, uncropped);
// this file is the tightly-cropped, downscaled render actually served.
// No SVG path data was available (ra.co blocks direct asset access and
// no official vector source could be found), so it's a raster PNG with
// its real alpha transparency preserved — filter: brightness(0)
// invert(1) turns the mark's real black fill white to match every other
// icon in this row, same technique, same visual result as an SVG
// fill="white" would give, without altering the mark's actual geometry.
---

<img
  class="ra-logo"
  src="/images/icons/resident-advisor.png"
  alt="Resident Advisor"
  width="240"
  height="114"
  loading="lazy"
/>

<style>
  /* Height (not the row's usual ~29px) chosen so the mark's real ~2.1:1
     aspect ratio doesn't render it much wider than its siblings — at 29px
     tall it would be ~61px wide vs. Beatport/EPK's ~23-36px. 18px keeps
     its rendered width in that same ~36-38px range instead. */
  .ra-logo {
    height: 18px;
    width: auto;
    display: block;
    filter: brightness(0) invert(1);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .ra-logo {
      height: 15px;
    }
  }
</style>
